
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `ar` baraye sakhtan, tagheer dadan, va estخراج (extract) kardan az archive-ha (file-haye jam' shode) estefade mishavad. In archive-ha baraye negahdari library-haye code estefade mishavand.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `ar -t archive.a` --> 📜 List kardan content-haye archive.
    🔹 `ar -x archive.a file1.o file2.o` --> 📦 Extract kardan `file1.o` va `file2.o` az archive.
    🔹 `ar -v` --> 👀 Verbose mode (namayesh etela'at bishtar dar morede amal).
    🔹 `ar -r archive.a file3.o` --> ➕ Replace (ya ezafe kardan) `file3.o` be archive.
    🔹 `ar -d archive.a file1.o` --> 🗑️ Delete kardan `file1.o` az archive.
    🔹 `ar -c archive.a file4.o` --> 🔨 Sakhtan archive agar vojood nadashte bashad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ ar -tv archive.a

    🔹 Namayesh verbose (detailed) listing az archive.

    $ ar -x archive.a

    🔹 Extract kardan hameye file-ha az archive.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ ar -r libmath.a add.o multiply.o

    🔹 Replace ya ezafe kardan `add.o` va `multiply.o` be archive `libmath.a`. Agar `libmath.a` vojood nadashte bashad, sakhte mishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `ar` command is used to create, modify, and extract from archives (collections of files). These archives are commonly used for storing object code libraries.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `ar -t archive.a` --> 📜 List the contents of the archive.
    🔹 `ar -x archive.a file1.o file2.o` --> 📦 Extract `file1.o` and `file2.o` from the archive.
    🔹 `ar -v` --> 👀 Verbose mode (show more information about the operation).
    🔹 `ar -r archive.a file3.o` --> ➕ Replace (or add) `file3.o` to the archive.
    🔹 `ar -d archive.a file1.o` --> 🗑️ Delete `file1.o` from the archive.
    🔹 `ar -c archive.a file4.o` --> 🔨 Create the archive if it doesn't already exist.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ ar -tv archive.a

    🔹 Shows a verbose (detailed) listing of the archive.

    $ ar -x archive.a

    🔹 Extracts all files from the archive.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ ar -r libmath.a add.o multiply.o

    🔹 Replaces or adds `add.o` and `multiply.o` to the archive `libmath.a`. If `libmath.a` does not exist, it will be created.
